<tr id="L474"><td><a href="#L474">474</a></td><td>JOSEPH:  I have fought the good fight. I have finished the course. I have kept the faith.</td></tr>

<tr id="L475"><td><a href="#L475">475</a></td><td>SISKO:  I've never known you to quote from the Bible.</td></tr>

<tr id="L476"><td><a href="#L476">476</a></td><td>JOSEPH:  I'm full of surprises, aren't I? And so are you. Sounds like that dream you had helped you sort things out.</td></tr>

<tr id="L477"><td><a href="#L477">477</a></td><td>SISKO:  I suppose it did. But I have begun to wonder. What if it wasn't a dream? What if this life we're leading, all of this, you and me, everything. What if all this is the illusion?</td></tr>

<tr id="L478"><td><a href="#L478">478</a></td><td>JOSEPH:  That's a scary thought.</td></tr>

<tr id="L479"><td><a href="#L479">479</a></td><td>SISKO:  I know, I know. But maybe, just maybe, Benny isn't the dream, we are. Maybe we're nothing more than figments of his imagination. For all we know, at this very moment, somewhere far beyond all those distant stars, Benny Russell is dreaming of us.</td></tr>

<tr id="L480"><td><a href="#L480">480</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Benny is Sisko's reflection in the window.</td></tr>

